## üì¶ MODULE 5: Authentication, Authorization & Security (Weeks 9‚Äì10)

### üü¢ Basics

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 1 | You need to secure your API so only authenticated users can access it. How do you implement JWT Bearer authentication in ASP.NET Core? |
| 2 | A user changes their role but the old JWT still grants them admin access. How does JWT expiry and token revocation work, and how do you solve this? |
| 3 | You need to protect certain endpoints so only users with `Admin` role can call them. How do you use `[Authorize(Roles = "Admin")]` and policy-based authorization? |
| 4 | Your app stores passwords. How do you use `ASP.NET Core Identity`'s `PasswordHasher` correctly and why should you never store plain text? |
| 5 | A penetration tester finds that your API is vulnerable to SQL injection via a search parameter. How do you fix it using parameterized queries or EF Core? |

### üü° Intermediate

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 6 | You need to implement OAuth2 + OpenID Connect with Azure AD as the identity provider. How do you configure it in ASP.NET Core and validate tokens? |
| 7 | Your API needs to support both Cookie auth (for MVC) and JWT auth (for mobile clients). How do you configure multiple authentication schemes? |
| 8 | A feature requires fine-grained permission checks (e.g., "can edit only their own orders"). How do you implement Resource-based Authorization using `IAuthorizationHandler`? |
| 9 | You need to implement Refresh Tokens securely. How do you store, rotate, and invalidate them to prevent token theft? |
| 10 | Your API is being hammered by a brute-force login attack. How do you implement account lockout, CAPTCHA, and IP rate limiting? |

### üî¥ Advanced

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 11 | You're building a multi-tenant SaaS. How do you implement tenant-based claims, isolate data per tenant, and prevent cross-tenant data leakage? |
| 12 | You need to implement a custom `IAuthorizationPolicyProvider` that loads policies dynamically from a database. Walk through the implementation. |
| 13 | Your security team requires all sensitive data (PII) to be encrypted at rest in SQL Server and in transit. How do you implement field-level encryption in EF Core? |
| 14 | How do you implement **Zero Trust** principles in your .NET microservices? (mTLS, service-to-service auth with Azure Managed Identity) |
| 15 | A GDPR audit requires you to implement the right to erasure. How do you design your .NET system to handle data deletion across multiple services and databases? |

