## üì¶ MODULE 6: Performance, Async & Concurrency (Weeks 11‚Äì12)

### üü¢ Basics

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 1 | Your API endpoint calls an external REST API synchronously, causing thread starvation. How do you convert it to `async/await` correctly? |
| 2 | A developer uses `.Result` on a `Task` inside an ASP.NET Core controller and the app deadlocks. Explain why and how to fix it. |
| 3 | You need to run 3 independent API calls in parallel and combine results. How do you use `Task.WhenAll()` correctly? |
| 4 | A background process needs to run every 5 minutes. How do you implement a `BackgroundService` or `IHostedService` in .NET? |
| 5 | Your endpoint is slow because it runs 5 sequential database queries. How do you identify which ones can run in parallel? |

### üü° Intermediate

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 6 | You need to process 10,000 records concurrently but limit to 10 at a time to avoid overloading downstream services. How do you use `SemaphoreSlim` or `Parallel.ForEachAsync`? |
| 7 | A memory profiler shows your app allocates excessive `Task` objects. How do you use `ValueTask` to reduce allocations in hot paths? |
| 8 | Multiple threads update a shared counter in a service. How do you choose between `lock`, `Interlocked`, and `ConcurrentDictionary`? |
| 9 | You need to implement a producer-consumer pipeline where producers publish messages faster than consumers process. How do you use `Channel<T>`? |
| 10 | Your app needs to cancel long-running operations (DB queries, HTTP calls) when a user disconnects. How do you propagate `CancellationToken` from the HTTP request through the call chain? |

### üî¥ Advanced

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 11 | A high-throughput API processes 50K requests/second. How do you use memory pooling (`ArrayPool<T>`, `MemoryPool<T>`) and `ObjectPool<T>` to reduce GC pressure? |
| 12 | You need to implement a lock-free queue for a real-time order matching engine. How do you use `ConcurrentQueue<T>` and compare it with `Channel<T>`? |
| 13 | Your .NET app has unpredictable GC pauses. How do you use `GC.TryStartNoGCRegion`, reduce LOH allocations, and tune GC settings in `runtimeconfig.json`? |
| 14 | You need to maximize CPU throughput for a CPU-bound computation. How do you use `Parallel.For`, `PLINQ`, and compare with `Task.Run` on a thread pool? |
| 15 | A real-time trading app needs sub-millisecond response times. How do you use `System.IO.Pipelines` to build a zero-copy network protocol parser? |

---

## üì¶ MODULE 7: Testing in .NET (Weeks 13‚Äì14)

### üü¢ Basics

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 1 | You need to write a unit test for an order calculation method. How do you set up an xUnit test project and write your first `[Fact]` and `[Theory]`? |
| 2 | Your service depends on `IEmailService`. How do you mock it using Moq and verify it was called with the correct parameters? |
| 3 | A bug was found where a discount is applied to zero-price items. How do you write a regression test to prevent this from happening again? |
| 4 | You need to test a method that throws an exception for invalid input. How do you assert exceptions in xUnit and FluentAssertions? |
| 5 | How do you test a controller action that returns `IActionResult`? What should you test vs. what should be in integration tests? |

### üü° Intermediate

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 6 | You need to integration test your API with a real database. How do you use `WebApplicationFactory<T>` and `TestContainers` for SQL Server? |
| 7 | A flaky test fails intermittently because it relies on `DateTime.Now`. How do you refactor using `IClock` abstraction and mock time in tests? |
| 8 | You need to test a MediatR handler chain including pipeline behaviors. How do you set up an in-memory MediatR test without mocking every piece? |
| 9 | Your team wants to enforce code coverage thresholds in CI. How do you configure Coverlet and report coverage in GitHub Actions? |
| 10 | How do you implement consumer-driven contract testing between your .NET API and a React frontend using Pact? |

### üî¥ Advanced

| # | Scenario-Based Question |
|---|------------------------|
| 11 | You need to test a RabbitMQ consumer. How do you use TestContainers with RabbitMQ and verify message processing end-to-end? |
| 12 | A chaos engineering requirement asks you to test how your service behaves when the database goes down mid-request. How do you simulate this with Polly and integration tests? |
| 13 | Your performance tests show p99 latency degraded after a recent deployment. How do you write benchmark tests using BenchmarkDotNet and integrate them into your CI pipeline? |
| 14 | You need to implement mutation testing to measure the quality of your test suite. How do you use Stryker.NET and interpret its results? |
| 15 | How do you implement Architecture Tests using NetArchTest or ArchUnitNET to enforce Clean Architecture rules (e.g., Domain layer must not depend on Infrastructure)? |

