## üó∫Ô∏è Summary Planner Overview

| Week | Module | Focus |
|------|--------|-------|
| 1‚Äì2 | C# Language Fundamentals | Value types, generics, async, Span, records |
| 3‚Äì4 | ASP.NET Core Web API | REST, middleware, caching, versioning |
| 5‚Äì6 | EF Core & SQL Server | Migrations, performance, concurrency |
| 7‚Äì8 | DI & Clean Architecture | MediatR, CQRS, Outbox, Vertical Slice |
| 9‚Äì10 | Security & Auth | JWT, OAuth2, RBAC, Zero Trust |
| 11‚Äì12 | Performance & Async | Channels, pooling, GC tuning, Pipelines |
| 13‚Äì14 | Testing | Unit, Integration, Contract, Mutation |

---

## üèÜ Pro Tips for Your Learning Path

> **As an 8-year veteran**, focus heavily on **Modules 4‚Äì7** (Architecture, Security, Performance, Testing) ‚Äî these will separate you from the crowd.

- üìå **Pair each scenario** with a real GitHub repo implementation
- üìå **Build a capstone project** ‚Äî an Order Management System using all modules
- üìå **Benchmark everything** ‚Äî use BenchmarkDotNet + dotnet-trace for profiling
- üìå **Write Architecture Decision Records (ADRs)** as you learn each pattern

